It amazes me how lame people can actually be, to justify BS like &quot;But I have a warrior twink who someday may be my main, and heck no druid loot dropped and I put in my time I should have the same right as someone else&quot;.  <br>
<br>
BS I say, you're a loot whore, and if you want a CoF for your twink, then start your own raid and make it absolutely clear that anyone has any right to any drop.   Other than that suck it up and don't complain.   There's some risk to going on dragon raids, one of those risks, which has ALWAYS been accepted was that there was a chance that what would suit the toon you took wouldn't drop.   To demand access to that which DOESN'T suit the toon you brought just because you didn't see stuff that DOES suit him is gay.<br>
<br>
Hi, I went on plenty of Nag raids in my early times, this was when red scale meant Red Dragonscale BP, not epic.  There were 2 things I was there for, the bag and the CoF.  If neither dropped great, grats to monk on GofM, Shaman on gay shaman thing, and so on and so forth.   I wasnt' going to get all huffy because what I could equip didn't drop and therefore demand the opportunity to have access to the stuff that DID, even if there were people there who needed.   ESPECIALLY for some twink.<br>
<br>
You want your twink warrior in a CoF from a pickup raid, then get him to the appropriate levels and have HIM raid, this isn't some druid solo camp where you can loot and scoot for twink gear.   <br>
