My god... I don't know if this can be belabored any longer. The reason you shouldn't be allowed to roll for your 60 warrior is because [bold]you are not there with your 60 warrior[/bold]. If your 60 warrior wants a CoF, he should save his pennies or go on a Talendor raid.<br>
<br>
Otherwise, it's pandemonium. Everyone will suddenly have alts no one knew about of varying levels.<br>
<br>
And I don't buy that the loot rules for that pickup raid suddenly &quot;changed&quot;. The original poster said he didn't know who the raid leader was. If he didn't know who the raid leader was, he couldn't POSSIBLY have been told what the loot rules were by the actual authority. Yes, I'm sure that the raid was full of attendees saying that it was FFA rolling on loot. However, I'd wager that the majority of those people were your standard pickup raid gibbering yardapes who think that if they SAY it's FFA loot often enough, it actually WILL be, regardless of reality.<br>
<br>
All that aside... The people who run around the game rolling on every possible thing they can get their greedy, sweaty little hands on make me sick and will be the first against the wall when the revolution comes. That kind of blind, mindless, idiotic loot steamshoveling is probably the best indicator of who you WOULDN'T want to know in RL.<br>
<br>
Yaen B`zhen<br>
